Political Capital: the Hungarian Guard increases country risk
According to the Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the Hungarian Guard’s activity, formed last August, with the support of Jobbik Magyarzózáczárt Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several respects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “risk warning,” the company notes that, in relation to the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “short-term aggressive ethnic confrontations can occur as a result of the exacerbation of ethnic tensions already existing between the Hungarian gypsy and non-gypsy population.”
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is likely to provoke this situation, is the main reason for this.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: “Public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groups that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Tsiganes and the Hungarians.”
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are getting stronger and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activities of the Hungarian Guard "have significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, particularly with regard to the country's confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
They recall that as a result of the increased publicity given to the reorganization of the Hungarian radical and far-right groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007, calling themselves the “national self-defense association”.
“The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization while publicly declaring the preparation of their members for defence missions (catastrophes, national defense, defense of order), armed, if necessary,” they said, in addition, by evoking the politicization of the impunity.
