What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, involves significant expenses that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the driver's license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange becomes responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in case of accident.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established by taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of driving licence, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rate to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of accidents than their prudence.
Similarly, using census reports, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his or her profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, it offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 have to face various disadvantages at the time of signing a contract with an affordable insurance, as may be the low driving experience and the old age of the driver's license.
While the ideal for being well-insured is insurance at all risk, other more economical options exist.
The most anticipated drivers can opt for any risk insurance with franchise, so they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of contract implies that the customer pays a part of the amount of the sin.
“The portion of the amount of the damage that the customer will pay will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be low,” said Luis Noguera, Spain’s First Europa manager, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be cautious and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the insurance price in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic fee that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” explains Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25, this becomes easier for drivers when signing a contract with insurance, as the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
This is why it is better to choose an all-risk insurance with a franchise.
"Young people can't normally enjoy the experience acquired before after an accident," said the director of the European company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, after the 'fear of the novice'.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is better that he negotiates insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest accident rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be a free-of-risk insurance (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have a more relaxed drive and they have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” judges Luis Noguera.
For retirees, insurance at all risk with franchise is preferable (when it is 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, so it is essential to study the insurance that is most appropriate for us according to our personal situation.
